20/10/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Incumbent Karolos Papoulias announced on Monday (October 19th) that he will run for re-election in the March 2010 presidential race. His candidacy enjoys the support of both the socialist PASOK party, led by Prime Minister George Papandreou, and the conservative New Democracy party of former Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis. Papoulias, 80, was elected president in 2005. (ANA-MPA, AP - 19/10/09)
